        <h2 style="text-align:center;font-size: 22px;color:cyan;font-family">Aloo Tikki</h2>

        <img style="padding-left:250px;" src="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQ8zQ0Ngssnpw42df7EbcIxgo04NPtxKtLkB0wsmV1mv4ctLkyqp4O52CMdeqwpAswNi0c&usqp=CAU" alt="Aloo Tikki">
        <div id="en">
            <h3>Ingredients:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>4 medium-sized potatoes</li>
                <li>1 small onion, finely chopped</li>
                <li>1-2 green chilies, finely chopped (adjust to taste)</li>
                <li>1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
                <li>1/2 teaspoon red chili powder (adjust to taste)</li>
                <li>1/2 teaspoon chat masala</li>
                <li>1/2 teaspoon garam masala</li>
                <li>1 teaspoon lemon juice</li>
                <li>Salt to taste</li>
                <li>Oil for shallow frying</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>Process:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Boil and Mash Potatoes:</strong><br />Boil the potatoes until they are soft. Allow them to cool, peel, and then mash them in a bowl. Make sure there are no lumps.</li>
                <li><strong>Prepare the Spice Mix:</strong><br />In a small bowl,mix red chili powder, chat masala,lemon juice,garam masala and salt.</li>
                <li><strong>Cook the Spice Mix:</strong><br />Heat a little oil in a pan and sauté the ginger-garlic paste and green chilies until the raw smell disappears. Add the spice mix and sauté for a minute. Then, add the finely chopped onions and cook until they turn soft and translucent.</li>
                <li><strong>Combine Ingredients:</strong><br />Add the spice mix to the mashed potatoes, Mix everything well.</li>
                <li><strong>Form Patties:</strong><br />Take a portion of the mixture and shape it into a round or oval patty. Repeat with the remaining mixture.</li>
                <li><strong>Shallow Fry:</strong><br />Heat a little oil in a frying pan over medium heat. Place the patties in the pan and cook until they turn golden brown on one side. Flip the patties and cook the other side until it's also golden brown. Add more oil as needed.</li>
                <li><strong>Serve Hot:</strong><br />Remove the Aloo Tikki from the pan and place them on a paper towel to drain excess oil. Serve hot with chutney or sauce of your choice.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Enjoy your homemade aloo tikki :)</p>
